This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with speech recognition and language identification. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) because it deals with acoustic signals. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing) because it deals with signal combination methods. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it compares the performance of different models. Finally, it could belong to cs.SD again because it deals with speech recognition and language identification, which are related to sound.
